						<summary>

						<p>On a broken slab lying near the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>The last four lines record gifts to the deities Śiva and Kēśava of Bāḍa. The top portion is lost. On palaeographical grounds the inscription may be assigned to the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
